# Dev server reload after implementation

When you **finish implementing or modifying web app code** in this repo, always refresh the local dev environment before ending your response.

## Required steps

Run from repo root (`/Users/dpark/Documents/P4_check.mate`):

```bash
npm run dev:web:clean
```

This kills any process on port 3004, deletes `apps/web/.next`, and starts a fresh Next.js dev server.

Run it **in the background** (`block_until_ms: 0`) and wait until `http://localhost:3004` responds (200 or expected redirect like 307 to `/login`).

## When to run

- After any task that changed files under `apps/web/`, `packages/server/`, or `packages/shared/` (anything the web app imports).
- Skip only for read-only Q&A with zero file edits.

## Tell the user

Confirm the server was restarted and share **http://localhost:3004** (and the relevant page path if applicable).
